41:31.906 --> 41:34.117
I'm really proud
to make it this far.

41:34.117 --> 41:35.785
To me, it's
a real acknowledgement

41:35.785 --> 41:37.704
that I have a skill
set for this,

41:37.704 --> 41:39.455
and I'm gonna keep pursuing it,

41:39.455 --> 41:44.419
<i>keep getting better,</i>
<i>learn from my mistakes.</i>

41:44.419 --> 41:46.129
- Chad, congratulations.
You are the new

41:46.129 --> 41:47.338
"Forged in Fire" champion.

41:47.338 --> 41:48.840
And that's a title that comes

41:48.840 --> 41:50.633
with a check for how much?
- 10,000.

41:50.633 --> 41:52.802
- That's right, $10,000.
Good job.

41:52.802 --> 41:55.346
Please present
your weapons to the judges.

41:55.346 --> 41:57.682
<i>- I'm feeling really good</i>
<i>right now.</i>

41:57.682 --> 42:00.268
It's--loss for words.

42:00.268 --> 42:03.062
Being "Forged in Fire"
champion is surreal.

42:03.062 --> 42:05.523
<i>I was able to show my best,</i>

42:05.523 --> 42:08.401
